definitions: To cause to pass quickly or imperceptibly.
To move or change the position of (a ship or part of a ship) by hauling on ropes or cables.
To take the skin off (an animal); to flay.
examples: The deer fleets through the forest.
Time fleets by when you're having fun.
He fleets the rope through the pulley.
The butcher fleets the hide from the carcass.
